value.0: The Living Guard are renowned for their skill, and despite the state of their former home, they remain dangerously organized.

This helmet has been exquisitely forged from adamantine, its sinisterly beautiful design typical of drow craftsmanship. A small letter "V" has been interwoven into the pattern upon the visor.

Adamantine is an extraordinarily hard alloy that is almost impenetrable to normal weapons. Deposits of adamant are usually found near areas of Faerzress in the Underdark, and to the Deep Denizens it is usually black in colour, though it possesses a green sheen when viewed by natural light or a purple-white sheen when viewed by magical light.

An obese hag in body and spirit. Bones and seaweed litter lanky hair. She waddles about on a wooden leg, the stink of salt and rotten fish wafting wherever she goes. She answers your examination with a lascivious grin through rotten teeth.

The cauchemar is a horrible, especially malevolent version of a nightmare. The sight of one of these great horrors bearing down is enough to shake the heart of the boldest champion.

A cauchemar nightmare is about the size of a light war horse.
